Beautiful burgundy colour without an ounce of carbonation (as foretold by many) with a robust aroma of figs, dried stone fruit and a variety of woods.  The slick mouthfeel finishes with none of the alcohol heat I'd expect from +12% ABV.  Taste has more depth & layers than I can begin to list, but combine to a warming and delicious well balanced barley "port".  The nicest port I've ever enjoyed!  This was a 2014 bottle that could have aged much longer. 561 charactershopsolutely, Jul 24, 2015
